Innovation to stay ahead of the curve in terms of catering to consumer tastes in a rapidly changing environment is slowly becoming the norm as local Kenyan beverage manufacturers angle to maintain and even grow market share. With a global focus on a shift towards spirits and a growing movement towards flavored variants, much loved Kenyan brands have held their own and even continued to grow. According to Kenya breweries limited, which is 70% of the East African business of the worldâ€™s largest spirits manufacturer and key beer maker Diageo, the shift in demographics towards millennials is driving new trends that place unique and diverse needs in the Kenyan marketplace.